	(1531,402,'activities_4_activity_description','In the final phase, we will allow some flexibility in the agenda.\r\nOur base case is that we do a short TV interview from either a Swiss or US perspective.\r\nTV interviews are an effective way of challenging participants to be pithy and concise in their answers, and to front load their most important content. This is crucial because you often have so little time on TV you need to deliver you key messages early in case you do not get a second chance. Of course, body language and voice control are also essential in this format.\r\nEqually, it may be that the delegates wish to practise a particular question or to go over some of the specific messages so they find a way of delivering them that feels absolutely right for them. We can accommodate either approach and will adjust as required.'),
