	(1551,404,'overview','The session began with a discussion on how you would need to callibrate your messages for the three separate locations.In each case you would need to show empathy for the audience, without making false promises or unrealistically raising expectations. It is important that nothing is said that could later be challenged as misinformation.Equally, you need to be seen as in control and providing a valuable source of information. It is also important to remember that you are unlikely to be the sole interviewee, and that other stakeholders will be asked for their views.\r\n\r\nAs part of the session we gave you an overview of how the media operates, and how reporters are, in essence, production workers who put together stories using the TRUTH criteria from information you supply. We then introduced the IMEAN method of interview preparation.'),
