	(1515,402,'activities_2_activity_description','The first Interview will be from the perspective of a well-informed business newswire. This is intended to be a run through of the most likely questions that the closure of the GEIS deal will generate. Indicative questions include:\r\n- How will you turn around what is in effect a failing division?\r\n- Why can you run IS better than GE?\r\n- Arent you going to be eaten alive by lower cost competitors from China?\r\n- How many people will lose their jobs?\r\n- You say you will be investing in R&amp;D  can you tell us how much the new R&amp;D budget will be?\r\n- How will ongoing cooperation with GE work?\r\nWouldnt a full merger of ABB and GE make sense ultimately, especially in line of GEs recent track record? (deliberately provocative question!)\r\nThis interview will be videoed and played back for constructive feedback'),
	(1514,402,'_activities_2_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
