	(1523,402,'activities_3_activity_description','The second interview will be from the perspective of The Atlanta Journal-Constitution. The idea here is to stimulate the delegates thinking about how to handle sensitive questions from local media who (a) may not fully understand the work of GEIS and (b) will be seeking reassurance about jobs. Likely question lines include:\r\n- What can you do to reassure local people worried about their jobs?\r\n- But its not a good look for a Swiss company to be transferring jobs out of the USA is it?\r\n- What does the future hold for GEIS after your takeover?\r\n- You talk about synergies  this simply means firing people, doesnt it?\r\n- Will GEIS still be an Atlanta company? Can you guarantee the future of the business here?\r\nThis interview will be videoed but the feedback is likely to be delivered without playback, to manage time and to reflect the way reporters usually construct stories by referring to their notes.'),
