	(2334,518,'activities_7_activity_description','Complex legal cases need careful explanations to a general audience; we will encourage the participants to get their outcomes delivered in short clips and with the intention of being easy to understand and memorable.\r\n\r\nWe will run a down-the-line scenario as well as some pre-rec clips. The coach will begin by talking through the set-up requirements of these types of interviews, and we will use the footage to analyse the success of the interview. Possible subjects include the Barclays trial, Brexit threat to cybersecurity, womens rights issues including FGM legislation and anything else thrown up by the news agenda of the day.'),
