	(1507,402,'activities_1_activity_description','In the next section, we intend to present a short piece of theory entitled The Clash of Agendas. This establishes a framework for understanding how journalists will approach the GEIS / ABB story, based on the incentives they face within the newsroom. It normally breaks down into three sections, although we adjust this phase in line with the experience levels of the participants.\r\n Power in the newsroom  What pressures does a journalist face and what are their prime motivators?\r\n The agenda of a journalist - How do those pressures manifest themselves? The journalist has an agenda  to write a good story - knowing what actually makes a good story can help manage the interview.\r\n Delivering your own agenda  This is the crux of our approach. We will ask the delegates to use the existing message house as a preparation tool for the interviews, so they stay on message and become as familiar as possible with the agreed narrative.\r\n30 '),
