	(2462,546,'_trainers','field_5b11084b0b702'),
	(2463,546,'overview','Dear Ellen,\r\n\r\nIt was good to meet you and thank you for your time and commitment during the recent media training session. We hope that you found the insight into the journalists agenda useful, and that you will be able to use some of the lessons learned in future engagements.\r\n\r\nIn this note, we capture the main feedback points from the session, where you performed well, and where there are areas to work on.\r\n\r\nWe recommend that you look back at your performances in the private portal we provide for you. Please click through the thumbnail on the portal.\r\n\r\n<b><i>Introduction</i></b>\r\n\r\nIn your session, we focused on the broadcast media and simulated a radio with Nicky Campbell on BBC Radio 5 Live and two TV interviews; a face-to-face studio interview with Kay Burley on Sky News and an interview for a clip with BBC News. We believe this approach gives our clients relevant insight and experience of the different demands of each format so that you can prepare appropriately.'),
	(2284,518,'activities_1_activity_name','Understanding the media: the clash of agendas'),
