	(2467,546,'more_work','<ul>\r\n 	<li>Be aware of your listening position; your mouth movements can betray your discomfort and the knowing nod can indicate agreement whilst listening to a negative question. We saw this in the opening question of the Sky News interview.</li>\r\n 	<li>You were right to correct the incorrect name of your firm  which can often happen in the news factory but please do not stop there! Make sure that you continue with your purpose in being there; to deliver your prepared messages. Correct promptly and continue.</li>\r\n 	<li>Correcting and pausing, as we saw, can cause the interviewer to set the agenda  and negatively  to ask about the wife-beaters you represent. We discussed how you could have returned to answering the first question on the importance of representation during cross-examination, rather than spend time justifying who you may or may not represent. Similarly, when given a helpful question in this regard, repeat and explain, rather than simply agree and stop, as we saw in the Five Live interview.</li>\r\n 	<li>Think of the shape of your mouth movements to help avoid the um you said concerns you. Although we advised that, you did not sound at all as you thought <em>and</em> that this can be managed with preparation. Although your red dress is great, you could consider a jacket to deal with the issue of microphone cables.</li>\r\n 	<li>Be careful about using emotive terms such as suffering in relation to lawyers. We discussed how you could have used the helicopter view to take the agenda back to the suffering of victims and children and how it is better for all to have legal representation.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
