	(3703,603,'activities_0_activity_name','Introductions and objective setting; Intro from Myddleton Communications'),
	(3704,603,'_activities_0_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(3705,603,'activities_0_activity_description','The Bladonmore team will introduce themselves and set some context for the session. We will welcome the Myddleton team to comment about the nature of the work that we do and that the purpose of the coaching is to arm the participants with the techniques and confidence to take advantage of media opportunities that will enable them to promote their own practices and the firms brand, and also to take on active competitors in their market.'),
	(3706,603,'_activities_0_activity_description','field_5b11098d14d46'),
	(3707,603,'activities_0_activity_start','13:00:00'),
	(3708,603,'_activities_0_activity_start','field_5b11105bbe3d5'),
	(3709,603,'activities_0_activity_end','13:10:00'),
	(3710,603,'_activities_0_activity_end','field_5b111097bf5d2'),
	(3711,603,'activities_1_activity_name','Understanding the media: the clash of agendas'),
	(3712,603,'_activities_1_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(3713,603,'activities_1_activity_description','We discussed in the briefing call that although John, Julian and Ellen have seen a short version of this presentation for the broadcast media, we believe that it will be helpful for them to see a more detailed illustration of how the <u>print</u> media operates and the pressures on journalists to get their stories published.\r\n\r\nWe will run through the newsroom drivers and how the individuals need to manage them, in conjunction with their advisers. The topics that we will cover are:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Power in the newsroom</strong>  What pressures does a journalist face and what are their prime motivators?</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>The agenda of a journalist</strong>  How do those pressures manifest themselves? The journalist has an agenda  to produce a good story that gets on the show. For delegates, knowing what actually makes a good story can help manage the interview.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Creating your own agenda</strong>  We will introduce the participants to the Bladonmore preparation process and give them time to work on some messages with support. We will then spend the rest of the session testing and refining these messages in various exercises.'),
	(3714,603,'_activities_1_activity_description','field_5b11098d14d46'),
	(3715,603,'activities_1_activity_start','13:10:00'),
	(3716,603,'_activities_1_activity_start','field_5b11105bbe3d5'),
	(3717,603,'activities_1_activity_end','13:40:00'),
	(3718,603,'_activities_1_activity_end','field_5b111097bf5d2'),
	(3719,603,'activities_2_activity_name','Exercise 1: National Newspaper Interviews - The Financial Times/The Guardian'),
	(3720,603,'_activities_2_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(3721,603,'activities_2_activity_description','We will ask the delegates to divide into two groups as follows:\r\n\r\nGroup 1: John, Jane, Shula and Richard\r\n\r\nGroup 2: Ellen, Julian, Rachel and Paul\r\n\r\nWe will explain that we are dividing them up so that they can gain the maximum benefit of the training; working together on four separate exercises and deciding each time who should represent the group, so every delegate will take part in at least one exercise.\r\n\r\nWe will remind the delegates that however specialist a journalist maybe, they will not possess their level of expertise and still need to speak in the language of the audience, which may be at a higher level of awareness than, for example, The Sun, but they are not practising lawyers at the top of their game. We will ask each group to brief a spokesperson for either of the above publications.'),
	(3722,603,'_activities_2_activity_description','field_5b11098d14d46'),
	(3723,603,'activities_2_activity_start','13:40:00'),
