	(4479,622,'activities_4_activity_name','Exercise 3: Pitching a story and gaining an interview with Regional Press'),
	(4480,622,'_activities_4_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(4481,622,'activities_4_activity_description','We will again ask delegates to split into groups and decide on two different spokespersons to initially pitch the story to the newsdesk and another to speak to a regional paper that they have strategically targeted. We will have explained the importance of offering local detail to a regional journalist, therefore this exercise is aimed at enabling the delegates to get BCL Solicitors into the regional headlines by offering journalists a story which will help their careers and build valuable relations with the firm.\r\n\r\nWe will suggest stories such as the surge in county lines networks  which gangs use to transport drugs out of cities to rural areas and which has been blamed for the increase in child drug offences across the country (West Mercia has seen a 42% y-o-y increase in drug offences committed by children aged between 10 and 17), or a fraud case in Manchester that involves local doctors. We will give the delegates time to develop a story and pitch it to a regional editor. We will film and review the exercise.'),
	(4482,622,'_activities_4_activity_description','field_5b11098d14d46'),
